The paper proposes a new ensemble method specialized for deep neural networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning and computer vision research. The paper also focuses on image classification and foreground-background segmentation tasks, which are common applications in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper introduces new loss, architecture, and training methods, which are related to optimization and neural network design, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques, such as multiple choice learning and stochastic labeling, which could be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
